obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42970)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Title.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42970&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Suits Valuation Act, 1887 ^1[and it extends^2`
  line `to the`
  line `whole of India except the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956,`
  line `were comprised in Part B States.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `2. Extended to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and Fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42971)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Extent and commencement of Part I.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42971&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `This Part shall extend to such local areas, and`
  line `come into force therein on such dates as the ^1[State Government], by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, directs.^2`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaption of Laws (No. 2) order, 1956, for "Government of a Part A State or a Part C State".`
  line
  line `2. Part I of the Act has, under s. 2, been declared to extend to the Punjab, and to come into force therein on the 1st day of`
  line `March, 1889, see Gazette of India, 1889, Pt. I, p. 107.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42972)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of State Government to make rules determining value of land for jurisdictional purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. The words "subject to the control of the G. G. in C." rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42972&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may ^1*** make rules for determining`
  line `the value of land for purposes of jurisdiction in the suits mentioned in the Court-fees`
  line `Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), section 7, paragraphs v and vi, and paragraph x, clause (d).`
  line
  line `(2) The rules may determine the value of any class of land, or of any interest in land, in the`
  line `whole or any part of a local area, and may prescribe different values for different places within`
  line `the same local area.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42973)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Valuation of relief in certain suits relating to land not to exceed the value of the land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42973&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Where a suit mentioned in the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), section 7, paragraph`
  line `iv, or Schedule II, article 17, relates to land or an interest in land of whi ch the value has`
  line `been determined by rules under the last foregoing section, the amount at which for purposes`
  line `of jurisdiction the relief sought in the suit is valued shall not exceed the value of the land or`
  line `interest as determined by those rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42974)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Making and enforcement of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42974&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, before making rules under`
  line `section 3, consult the High Court with respect thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) A rule under that section shall not take effect till the expiration of one month after`
  line `the rule has been published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42975)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Repeal of section 14 of the Madras Civil Courts Act, 1873.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42975&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On and from the date`
  line `on which rules under section 3 take effect in any part of the territories under the`
  line `administration of the Governor of Fort Saint George in Council to which the Madras Civil Courts Act, 1873, (3 of 1873), extends, section 14 of that Act shall be repealed as regards`
  line `that part of those territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42976)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Extent and commencement of Part II.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42976&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `This Part ^1*** shall come into force on the first day of`
  line `July, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "extends to the whole of India except Part B States and" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws`
  line `(No. 2) Order, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42977)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Court-fee value and jurisdictional value to be the same in certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42977&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Where in`
  line `suits other than those referred to in the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870),`
  line `section 7, paragraphs v, vi and ix, and paragraph x, clause (d), court-fees are payable ad`
  line `valorem under the Court-fees Act, 1870, the value as determinable for the computation of`
  line `court-fees and the value for purposes of jurisdiction shall be the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42978)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Determination of value of certain suits by High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42978&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `When the subject-matter of`
  line `suits of any class, other than suits mentioned in the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870),`
  line `section 7, paragraphs v and vi, and paragraph x, clause (d), is such that in the opinion of the`
  line `High Court it does not admit of being satisfactorily valued, the High Court may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the State Government, direct that suits of that class shall, for the`
  line `purposes of the Court-fees Act, 1870, and of this Act and any other enactment for the time`
  line `being in force, be treated as if their subject-matter were of such value as the High Court`
  line `thinks fit to specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42979)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42979&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of s. 32 of the Punjab Courts Act, 1884 (18 of 1884).] Rep. by the Repealing`
  line `and Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891), s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42980)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure where objection is taken on appeal or revision that a suit or appeal was not properly valued for jurisdictional purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42980&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `in ^1section 578 of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882), an objection that by reason of`
  line `the over-valuation or under-valuation of a suit or appeal a Court of first instance or lower`
  line `Appellate Court which had not jurisdiction with respect to the suit or appeal exercised`
  line `jurisdiction with respect thereto shall not be entertained by an Appellate Court unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the objection was taken in the Court of first instance at or before the`
  line `hearing at which issues were first framed and recorded, or in the lower Appellate`
  line `Court in the memorandum of appeal to that Court, or`
  line
  line `(b) the Appellate Court is satisfied, for reasons to be recorded by it in writing, that`
  line `the suit or appeal was over-valued or under-valued, an that the over-valuation or`
  line `under-valuation thereof has prejudicially affected the disposal of the s uit or appeal on its`
  line merits.
  line
  line `(2) If the objection was taken in the manner mentioned in clause ( a) of sub-section (1),`
  line `but the Appellate Court is not satisfied as to both the matters mentioned in clause ( b) of that`
  line `sub-section and has before it the materials necessary for the determination of the other`
  line `grounds of appeal to itself, it shall dispose of the appeal as if there had been no defect of jurisdiction in`
  line `the Court of first instance or lower Appellate Court.`
  line
  line `(3) If the objection was taken in that manner and the Appellate Court is satisfied as to both`
  line `those matters and has not those materials before it, it shall proceed to deal with the appeal under`
  line `the rules applicable to the Court with respect to the hearing of appeals; but if it remands the suit or`
  line `appeal, or frames and refers issues for trial, or requires additional evidence to be taken, it shall`
  line `direct its order to a Court competent to entertain the suit or appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section with respect to an Appellate Court shall, so far as they can`
  line `be made applicable, apply to a Court exercising revisional jurisdiction under ^2section 622 of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882) or other enactment for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(5) This section ^3*** shall come into force on the first day of July, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now s. 99 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `2. See now s. 115 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `3. The words "extends to the whole of India except Part B States and" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2)`
  line `Order, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42981)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Proceedings pending at commencement of Part I or Part II.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317&sectionId=42981&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00009_188707_1523273588317
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Part I or Part II shall`
  line `be construed to affect the jurisdiction of any Court--`
  line
  line `(a) with respect to any suit instituted before rules under Part I applicable to the`
  line `valuation of the suit take effect, or Part II has come into force, as the case may be, or`
  line
  line `(b) with respect to any appeal arising out of any such suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
